petascope_metadata_schema.sh script is used for generating the petascope schema into the schema/ folder
It uses SchemaSpy, which can be obtained from http://schemaspy.sourceforge.net/

Usage:
./petascope_metadata_schema.sh SchemaSpy.jar postgresql.jar Settings_file
where:
  - SchemaSpy.jar is the location of the SchemaSpy jar file
  - postgresql.jar is the location of the postgresql driver jar file, usually found at $RASDAMAN/applications/petascope/lib/postgresql-...jar
  - Settings_file is the location of the petascope.properties file ($RMANHOME/etc/petascope.properties)

Example:
./petascope_metadata_schema.sh schemaSpy_5.0.0.jar postgresql.jar petascope.properties
